<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-10-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-10-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="536" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d536">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Taylor</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">San Sebastian</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-10-11"><hi rend="italic">October 11,
                                1896</hi></date>. (Received Oct. 26.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 572.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that I have
                            received from the minister of state a note dated the 8th ultimo,
                            informing me that on the 17th of July last the military authorities of
                            the Island of Cuba transferred the proceedings against the American
                            citizen Francis J. Larrieu to the ordinary or civil jurisdiction.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hannis Taylor.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>